5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 402, L.D. 912, “An Act to Address the
10 Use of Electricity by Data Centers”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Limit the Amount of Electricity That May Be Provided to Data Centers on
13 a Certain Commercial or Industrial Site'
14 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
15 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
16 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
17 Whereas, economic development in certain areas of the State requires ensuring that
18 energy resources are available to a variety of employers and industries; and
19 Whereas, this legislation is immediately necessary to ensure that local sources of
20 electricity generation are not monopolized by data centers; and
21 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
22 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
23 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
24 therefore,'
25 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
26 following:
27 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §102, sub-§20-B, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 205, §2, is
28 amended to read:
29 B. The entity's tenants; or
30 Sec. 2. 35-A MRSA §102, sub-§20-B, ¶C, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 205, §2, is
31 repealed and the following enacted in its place:
32 C. Commercial or industrial consumers located on the property where the entity is
33 located or on abutting property; or
Page 1 - 132LR1873(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 402, L.D. 912
1 Sec. 3. 35-A MRSA §102, sub-§20-B, ¶D is enacted to read:
2 D. Commercial or industrial consumers located on a commercial or industrial site
3 within the control area of the New England independent system operator and located
4 in a municipality north of the Town of Chester that was served by the entity or its
5 predecessor without using the transmission and distribution plant of a public utility
6 prior to December 31, 2018. The exception under this paragraph does not apply if
7 more than 25% of the nameplate capacity of the entity is used to serve data centers
8 located on the commercial or industrial site. For the purposes of this paragraph, "data
9 center" means any facility in the State, which may be a freestanding structure or a
10 facility within a larger structure, that primarily contains electronic equipment used to
11 process, store and transmit digital information that uses environmental control
12 equipment to maintain the proper conditions for the operation of electronic equipment.'
13 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
14 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
15 takes effect when approved.'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment replaces the bill, changes the title and adds an emergency preamble
2200 and emergency clause. It amends an existing statutory exception to the definition of
2211 "transmission and distribution utility" for certain entities on commercial or industrial sites
2222 to provide that an entity that otherwise would qualify for the exception must be located
2233 within the control area of the New England independent system operator in a municipality
2244 north of the Town of Chester and may not use more than 25% of its nameplate capacity to
2255 serve data centers located on the commercial or industrial site.
